<span class=title> Re: Group-friendly wizard buff-like attack spells</span><hr size=1> When you say imbuing weapons that makes it an enchanter spell.  BUT, if you make them evocation based and call them channeling of power then its wizard based sence wizards are the masters of the elements even more so then mages with our wide variety of access to different forms of magic, fire, cold damage.  <br>
<br>
So if you bill it as channeling verious elements into the weapons then no I don't see it as an enchanter spell.  If you bill it as just imbuing a weapon with magic energy only not fire or cold and making it an alteration spell then yes id see it as an enchanter spell.<br>
<br>
Wizards are constantly channelng mana to form verious cold fire or magic based attacks.  I don't see a wizard channeling mana to create an aura of fire or ice or magic around a weapon to far off from what we already do.  This is purely 100% a damage buff and enchanters don't use the elements like we do so this is not an enchanter spell in my opinion.<br>
<br>
And yes most wizards don't want to be buff bots so for this to fly it would have to have a very low mana cost a fast cast time and a duration of 20-30 minutes and a requirement of grouping with the person.  Any longer then that and it starts to get sold in the nexus.<br>
<br>
Also the percentage thing wouldn't work.  You'd need to make set amounts at each level and it would basicaly be an added proc to the weapon and would only proc the damage at the rate the character its cast on might normaly proc and would stack with other procs already on the weapons.<br>
<br>
Now I don't see it as unresonable to make this spell extreamly low on mana cost, heck even a mana cost of 1 sence you can only use it in a group or on yourself, and sence you don't melle and your normal chance of procing is low it is useless for soloing as a wizard even at level 1.  <br>
<br>
What I would do to make this spell work is make it group only, give it a 15 minute duration, a 14.5 minute refresh timer and only castable in group.  Also a mana cost of 1 and a cast time of 3 seconds.  Then it wouldn't be sold in nexus it would be a great help to groups it wouldn't cost us anything to cast it and we'd only be able to buff one person and wouldn't be buff botting a whole raid.  Down side, we lose a spell slot when in a group.  Up side groups are more interested in having a wizard for the extra proc damage / agro. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=artillis>Artillis</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<BR>Enjoys Sheep Erotica</span><br>  Posts: 1767<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/28/03 3:23:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26302.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Group-friendly wizard buff-like attack spells</span><hr size=1> Ohh id like to add we already do have damage buffs we can cast on others, the Okiels line.  So these proc spells would basicaly be just like the okeils line if you think about it, just a different way of dealing damage. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=myztic>MyztiC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>Born-Again Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 888<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/28/03 3:49:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26302.topic&index=21>Reply<